  "read": "TileLang sparse-MLA backward probability recompute slab producer with per-route selected-limit metadata. It consumes real q/dO/output/lse plus compressed KV and packed group ids, computes dO.output once per token, recomputes QK and dO.KV once per token/selected tile, then writes packed BF16 P and scaled dP slabs as [2, S, topk, H]. It intentionally does not compute dKV; this measures whether an adjacent P/dP producer plus the existing selected-limit dKV consumer is viable, or whether P/dP must be consumed on-chip inside the dKV producer. This run feeds real TorchTitan sparse-MLA boundary tensors into the TileLang dKV producer. Materialized per-head probs and scaled grad_logits are present only for materialized-input modes or correctness-reference checks; recompute mode uses q/dO/output/lse/compressed KV in the timed producer.",
